{
  "global": "Patch Axes.cla() and Figure.clf() to unset the .axes and .figure attributes on all contained artists before clearing, mirroring the behavior already present in Artist.remove().",
  "subtasks": [
    {
      "subtask": "Locate the remove() implementation to understand how it unsets artist attributes",
      "atomics": [
        "Search matplotlib/artist.py for 'def remove' and read the method body",
        "Identify which attribute assignments (self.axes = None, self.figure = None) are made and under what conditions"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Locate and read Axes.cla() to understand what artists it owns and how it clears them",
      "atomics": [
        "Search matplotlib/axes/_base.py for 'def cla' and read the full method",
        "Enumerate all artist container attributes cleared by cla() (self.lines, self.patches, self.collections, self.images, self.texts, self.artists, etc.)",
        "Identify the point in cla() just before containers are reset where unset logic should be inserted"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Modify Axes.cla() to unset .axes on all deparented artists",
      "atomics": [
        "Before the container reset lines in cla(), iterate over every artist container and call 'artist.axes = None' (or the appropriate private setter) on each element",
        "Ensure the iteration covers all containers: lines, patches, images, collections, texts, tables, artists, and any legend"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Locate and read Figure.clf() and modify it to unset .figure on all deparented artists",
      "atomics": [
        "Search matplotlib/figure.py for 'def clf' and read the full method",
        "Identify all figure-level artist containers cleared by clf() (self.axes list, self.lines, self.patches, self.images, self.texts, self.legends, etc.)",
        "Before containers are reset, iterate over each artist and set 'artist.figure = None', also iterate over each axes' artists and set both 'artist.axes = None' and 'artist.figure = None'"
      ]
    },
    {
      "subtask": "Write regression tests for the new behaviour",
      "atomics": [
        "In the appropriate test file (e.g. lib/matplotlib/tests/test_axes.py), add a test that calls a.cla() after a.plot() and asserts l.axes is None",
        "Add a test that calls f.clf() after plotting and asserts both l.axes is None and l.figure is None",
        "Run the new tests plus the existing axes/figure test suite to confirm no regressions"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "global_atomics": [
    "Run 'python -c \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt; f,a=plt.subplots(); l,=a.plot([1,2]); a.cla(); assert l.axes is None\"' to verify the cla() fix end-to-end",
    "Run 'python -c \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt; f,a=plt.subplots(); l,=a.plot([1,2]); f.clf(); assert l.figure is None\"' to verify the clf() fix end-to-end"
  ]
}

